    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-06-30T17:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-06-30T17:56:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <head>139. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d139fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66,
                            <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> 9 <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                            >PAK</gloss>. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Limdis1">Limdis</gloss>. Drafted
                        by <persName corresp="#p_MTC1">Mann</persName>, cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_KRW1">Komer</persName>, and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MTC1">Mann</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-06-30T18:56:00-04:00">June 30, 1965, 6:56 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1485. Please inform Minister Finance <persName corresp="#p_SM1"
                    >Shoaib</persName>, and in your discretion President Ayub, that given fact that
                    US Congress has not yet completed its authorization action on aid bill, given
                    fact that after authorization process is completed it will be necessary to go
                    through a separate appropriation procedure in the Congress, given reluctance of
                    the Administration to make a pledge in advance of action by the Congress, and in
                    view of certain other problems which we would be prepared to discuss with <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> should it wish, US is suggesting to World Bank
                    that date of consortium meeting be postponed until after Congress adjourns. US
                    thinking is that date of 27 September would allow adequate leeway and is so
                    proposing to Bank.</p>
                <p>You should also say that while postponement of consortium meeting will ultimately
                    become public knowledge, our suggestion is that both <gloss target="#t_USG1"
                        >USG</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> should avoid premature
                    publicity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
